2026-05-17 05:42:49 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #5 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"intent": "Select most northern Maltese Homo sapiens Neolithic sample (tie by later calendar year) and then find max aluminum in climateMeasurements at closest climate calendar year(s) to that sample year; output max aluminum rounded to 4 decimals.", "code": "import pandas as pd\n\nrad_path = '/home/ec2-user/eval_eqa/exploratory-qa-eval/.sandbox_isolated/task_1661820_1778996540167/kramabench-archeology-hard-5/files/radiocarbon_database_regional.xlsx'\nclim_path = '/home/ec2-user/eval_eqa/exploratory-qa-eval/.sandbox_isolated/task_1661820_1778996540167/kramabench-archeology-hard-5/files/climateMeasurements.xlsx'\n\n# Load radiocarbon\nrad = pd.read_excel(rad_path, sheet_name=0)\n\n# Normalize column names (keep as-is but handle spaces)\nrad.columns = [c.strip() for c in rad.columns]\n\n# Filter to Maltese dataset: Region == 'Maltese' likely; also ensure Homo sapiens and Neolithic\n# Use flexible: try if 'Region' contains 'Maltese'\nif 'Region' in rad.columns:\n    malt = rad[rad['Region'].astype(str).str.contains('Maltese', case=False, na=False)].copy()\nelse:\n    malt = rad.copy()\n\n# Filter species and culture\nmalt = malt[malt['Species'].astype(str).str.strip().str.lower().eq('homo sapiens')]\nmalt = malt[malt['Culture'].astype(str).str.contains('Neolithic', case=False, na=False)]\n\n# Determine latitude column\nlat_col = 'Latitude' if 'Latitude' in malt.columns else None\nassert lat_col is not None\n\n# Calendar year: use mean of 'Cal. BC 1 sigma' bounds if present.\n# But instructions say convert climate ages to calendar years; for radiocarbon tie-break by later calendar year.\n# We'll parse Cal. BC 1 sigma first; if empty, use Cal. BC 2 sigma.\n\ndef parse_range_to_mean(s):\n    if pd.isna(s):\n        return None\n    s = str(s)\n    # remove spaces\n    s = s.replace(' ', '')\n    # range like '6211-6011' or '62